 meant for L35 to L70 characters camped by players well beyond L100. It's just bullshit, and cheap, tacky bullshit at that. I saw one toon of L143 camping out in the Lab Director's office.<br><br>There needs to be a level cap on entry, like say nobody over L100, and Steps should be capped as well.<br><br>No, don't even <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> try</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to tell me there is nothing else for them to do, that dog won't hunt. Players of that level have the cyborg dungeon in Greater Tir County, just tailor-made for them. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=publius>Publius</A> at: 1/12/02 11:10:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/udharkaronavenger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DharkaronAvenger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#660000>(1/12/02 1:15:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1591.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dungeon in TLR</span><hr size=1> Well, the loot in the cyborg dungeon sucks, and the loot in the new dungeon is really pretty nice sometimes, although of course none of it is for MAs. By the way, has anyone tried the tank armor that drops off the bodyguards near the boss's office? I think it's called &quot;Assault Tank Armor&quot;, and the description says that it absorbs 2000 damage with a recharge time of 40 mins. That would be very useful if it weren't Enforcer only :P <p><img src="http://www.theinstitutes.com/ris/images/baiadin_id.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kitecheki>kitecheki</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#660000>(1/12/02 3:44:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1591.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dungeon in TLR</span><hr size=1> Im not all that excited about anything static(dungeons/missions).This one BIG reason I left Everquest.<br><br>I joined AO because they promised a world that lived and breathed.<br><br>Screw the static!It dosnt promote change.LOL are GMs/ARKs just bug recepticles?One thing FC said was they had learned from others mistakes!Well they havnt and they are heading down the same OLD boring road of static crap.<br><br>Trade skill items should be over and above what could ever be found in a dungeon.Imagine two or three skilled tradesmen working together to make you uber &quot;Gloves of Butt Spanking&quot;,for a hefty price of coarse.<br><br>Publius....Yes,regardless of what lvl a dungeon is made for,there will ALWAYS be higher lvls/guilds farming the static crap within it.That is why static loot dungeons and missions are a poor idea.<br><br>The sad fact is FC have so many talented ppl at their disposal,from coders to ARKS to make this game special,yet have chosen to take the quick boring and meaningless way of static gameplay.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=publius>Publius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>They call me Bruce.</span><br>  Posts: 272<br> <font color=#660000>(1/12/02 7:48:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1591.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dungeon in TLR</span><hr size=1> <!